05:52.520 --> 05:54.187
Earlier in our show,
we talked about

05:54.221 --> 05:55.923
transitions in sexuality.

05:55.956 --> 05:57.725
Uh, but what about race?

05:57.758 --> 06:00.193
Our correspondent,
Nathan Wielder,

06:00.227 --> 06:01.395
has the story.

06:10.370 --> 06:11.939
Harrison looks from the outside

06:11.972 --> 06:13.707
to be your average teenager.

06:13.741 --> 06:16.410
He goes to school,
plays video games,

06:16.444 --> 06:19.112
even listens to music
in his room.

06:19.146 --> 06:20.848
But there's one difference.

06:20.881 --> 06:23.451
I'm a 35-year-old white man.

06:23.484 --> 06:25.886
NATHAN: Harrison,
born Antwoine Smalls,

06:25.919 --> 06:27.855
has trans-racial identity,

06:27.888 --> 06:29.590
identifying as Harrison Booth,

06:29.623 --> 06:32.893
a 35-year-old white man
from Colorado.

06:32.926 --> 06:34.394
And when did you know
that you were a

06:34.428 --> 06:36.029
35-year-old white man?

06:36.063 --> 06:37.565
Well, I've always
felt different.

06:37.598 --> 06:39.967
I go to the store,
the movies,

06:40.000 --> 06:41.535
and just be thinking
to myself, like,

06:41.569 --> 06:44.738
"Why am I not getting
the respect I deserve?"

06:44.772 --> 06:47.908
And then,
it just hit me.

06:47.941 --> 06:50.043
I'm white...

06:50.077 --> 06:51.779
and 35.

06:51.812 --> 06:53.881
I just miss Colorado sometimes,
you know.

06:53.914 --> 06:55.749
Here, I pretend the buildings
are the old

06:55.783 --> 06:58.385
San Juan Mountain ranges but,
you know, the jobs is here.

06:58.418 --> 06:59.820
And where do you work?

06:59.853 --> 07:01.589
I'm a Systems Engineer
for Coca-Cola.

07:01.622 --> 07:02.556
Oh. Okay.

07:02.590 --> 07:03.791
That boy don't work.

07:03.824 --> 07:05.392
He go to school,
and that's it.

07:05.425 --> 07:06.594
-Mm-hmm.
-One day, he said,

07:06.627 --> 07:08.261
"Call me Harrison."

07:08.295 --> 07:10.230
I said, "Who's that?"

07:10.263 --> 07:11.632
He said, "Me."

07:11.665 --> 07:14.134
Do you believe
that he is a white man?

07:14.167 --> 07:15.769
I mean, he isn't.

07:15.803 --> 07:17.638
(bleep), I'd love
to wake up one day and say,

07:17.671 --> 07:19.840
"Hey, everybody,
I'm Rihanna."

07:19.873 --> 07:20.841
But I ain't.

07:20.874 --> 07:21.842
It's been pretty hard.

07:21.875 --> 07:23.677
My family just doesn't get it.

07:23.711 --> 07:25.913
You know, I try to get them
to go out with me,

07:25.946 --> 07:28.081
go on walks,
go to the farmers market,

07:28.115 --> 07:30.951
chat with people,
but...yeah.

07:30.984 --> 07:33.787
So why don't you think
that they get it?

07:33.821 --> 07:35.523
I don't think
they get it because

07:35.556 --> 07:37.858
they don't realize that race
is just a made-up thing.

07:37.891 --> 07:39.092
Mm-hmm.

07:39.126 --> 07:40.427
They grew up
having labels, and me,

07:40.460 --> 07:41.829
I'm just--I'm just
not like that.

07:41.862 --> 07:43.163
I see.

07:43.196 --> 07:45.499
So how do you embrace
your identity?

07:45.533 --> 07:47.000
-I dress a certain way.
-Ah.

07:47.034 --> 07:48.201
Patagonia.

07:48.235 --> 07:50.137
I wear a thick,
brown leather belt.

07:50.170 --> 07:52.439
I like to envision myself
after the surgery.

07:52.472 --> 07:53.941
(clears throat)

07:53.974 --> 07:57.344
"Hey, excuse me,
what IPA do you have on tap?"

07:57.377 --> 08:01.615
"Hey, did you see
Game of Thrones last night?"

08:01.649 --> 08:03.116
Yeah.

08:03.150 --> 08:04.818
So your--
your surgery,

08:04.852 --> 08:05.986
that's later this year?

08:06.019 --> 08:07.320
Right.
I started working

08:07.354 --> 08:09.056
at Stonecrest Mall,
so hopefully

08:09.089 --> 08:11.158
by then I have enough money
to take the next step.

08:11.191 --> 08:12.526
Mm-hmm.

08:12.560 --> 08:15.896
So you work at Coca-Cola
and the mall?

08:15.929 --> 08:19.199
Right.
Correct, I work at both.

08:19.232 --> 08:21.001
NATHAN: Harrison
has been planning

08:21.034 --> 08:23.804
a full racial transition
with a Dr. Samuel Vergara

08:23.837 --> 08:25.639
who guarantees Harrison
can visually transition

08:25.673 --> 08:27.474
through an experimental
procedure

08:27.507 --> 08:29.810
that will allow Harrison
not only to be a white man

08:29.843 --> 08:31.378
but whatever race he chooses.

08:31.411 --> 08:35.382
The procedure's
absolutely 100% possible.

08:35.415 --> 08:37.685
He's gonna look weird though.

08:37.718 --> 08:39.486
NATHAN: But before Harrison
can fully realize

08:39.519 --> 08:42.189
his physical identity,
he still has the day-to-day

08:42.222 --> 08:44.892
that's filled with
discrimination and ridicule.

08:44.925 --> 08:46.359
It--it's pretty awful,
you know.

08:46.393 --> 08:48.061
You--you walk
in the streets,

08:48.095 --> 08:50.263
and black people, they see you,
they nod to you like,

08:50.297 --> 08:52.032
"Hey, good to see us."

08:52.065 --> 08:54.267
And it's to the point
where I've just given up.

08:54.301 --> 08:56.003
I've stopped trying
to convince them

08:56.036 --> 08:58.739
-that I'm not "us."
-Gotcha.

08:58.772 --> 09:01.074
Hey, excuse me,
this is definitely the guy.

09:01.108 --> 09:03.110
He doesn't even live
in the area.

09:03.143 --> 09:04.745
I've never seen him before.

09:09.149 --> 09:12.119
(police radio chatter)

09:12.152 --> 09:14.054
